Eventhough police records have more words than those of the prossecutor office, the majority of data is between quartiles $q_1$ to $q_3$ in values from 32 to 214. What's more number of words above 390 would correspond to outliers. What is interesting is to notice that police records havea $q_1$ of 97 which is better for our training and predictions. Also it is interseting to notice that we could suggest that the distance between $q1$ and $q3$ from any of the subsets is similar $d_{q_1-q_3}^{fge} \approx d_{q_1-q_3}^{pol}$

In [ ]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def print_boxplot_characteristics(df, column_name):
    # calculate the lower fence, quartiles, mean, and upper fence
    q1 = np.percentile(df[column_name], 25)
    q2 = np.percentile(df[column_name], 50)
    q3 = np.percentile(df[column_name], 75)
    iqr = q3 - q1
    lower_fence = q1 - 1.5 * iqr
    upper_fence = q3 + 1.5 * iqr
    mean = df[column_name].mean()

    # print the results
    print(f'Lower fence: {lower_fence:.2f}')
    print(f'Q1: {q1:.2f}')
    print(f'Q2 (median): {q2:.2f}')
    print(f'Q3: {q3:.2f}')
    print(f'Upper fence: {upper_fence:.2f}')
    print(f'Mean: {mean:.2f}')

print("Caracteristicas relato Policia")
print_boxplot_characteristics(df=robos_df, column_name='cantidadPalabras_RelatoPolicia')
print("Características Relato Fiscalia")
print_boxplot_characteristics(df=robos_df, column_name='cantidadPalabras_RelatoFiscalia')

Since crime reports with a number of words below 97 do not have enough information for our task and because the boxplot shows that above 390 words are outliers (i.e. these reports are not so common in the digital records in siaf) I come to the conclusion of using

$data_i \in \; \mathcal{D} \; if\; len(data_i) \in 50<wordCound\leq 390$

Transforming dataset to have only one column of text¶

Let us formalize how we are about to deal with data. Data is organized by the number of the crime notice named $ndd$. We have that for a record $ndd_i$ it is possible to find two accepted crime tales, one from fge and another from police. This could be named $text^{fge}_i$ and $text^{pol}_i$. Since $ndd_i$ is not important for training we should check that create a new row like a new case but with the other text and must be careful to notice they have the same label. Otherwise we may compromise the correct training of the model. Also for training and validation it could be handed that we have samples from both types of tales

Organizing Delitos Validados Categories¶

A total of 48 different categories are found in data related to delitos_validados. According to analysis presented in notebook_RobosComisionDelitosValidadosAnalisis.html, we will proceed as follows:

  1. All crime categories that do not belong to any of the accepted 14 categories are removed. We retain the category Otros Robos but we must point that such catgory has not been checked. A second approach would be to discard it as well

  2. Now all remaining categories of delitos validados that belong to the new group of OTROS ROBOS will be renamed as OTROS ROBOS (e.g. Robo a instituciones de salud, Robo en ejes viales, and so on)

  3. If we have a remaining of SIN INFORMACION in delitos_seguimiento we count the number of samples and remove them

  4. Finally we make the datasets to train a new model in delitos_sequimiento and delitos_validados

Randomized Dataset¶

We have to remember that the dataset was ordered according to NDD, previously, in order to prevent that the categories in delitos seguimiento and delitos validados would be ordered for training we should proceed to randomize the dataset
